        <Parent_String>Leporidae (family) [300250215], Lagomorpha (order) [300310329], Mammalia (class) [300265707], Vertebrata (subphylum) [300265720], Chordata (phylum) [300266513], Animalia (kingdom) [300249395], Eukaryota (domain) [300265677], living organisms (entities) [300390503], Living Organisms (hierarchy name) [300265673], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term referring to mammals belonging to any of several genera containing around 30 species of Leporids, having long ears, a divided upper lip, and long hind legs adopated for leaping, differing from hares in being smaller and having thier young born naked and blind.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>數個屬約三十種兔類哺乳類動物的統稱，耳長，上唇分裂，後肢長，適於跳躍。與野兔不同，兔的身軀較小，其幼獸剛出生時全身無毛，而且眼睛看不見。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Término general que se refiere a los mamíferos pertenecientes a cualquiera de varios géneros que contienen alrededor de 30 especies de lepóridos, con orejas largas, labio superior dividido y largas patas traseras adoquinadas para saltar, que se diferencian de las liebres por ser más pequeñas y tener sus crías nacidas desnudas y ciegas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tlahtolli tlen quimanextia nochi tecuanimeh tlen tlachichitiah, zan catlinya tecuani huan oncah nechca quence 30 tlamantli tecuanimeh tlen cuatochimeh (lepóridos) ica ininnacaz huehhuehueyac, inintecomich quence moxelohtoc huan huehhuehueyac ininicxi tlen ica cuahuitonih, axcencah ica liebres pampa inihhuantin achi cuecuetztzitzin huan ininconehuan xolotiqueh huan axtlachiya quemman ontlacaquih.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
